{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17502265","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17502265"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:41:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:41:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1840"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1840","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1840"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.05,0.54,0.27,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1840"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78509"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1840","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1840"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1840"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63850"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"460"},{"type":"tags","id":"1217"},{"type":"tags","id":"3460"},{"type":"tags","id":"4208"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"12911"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"},{"type":"tags","id":"12922"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"4162"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4163"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26886"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39241"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78509","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78509"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 46-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-day history of intermittent right upper quadrant pain. Each episode lasts approximately one hour before resolving spontaneously. She is currently symptom-free. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her abdomen is soft and non-tender. An ultrasound examination is performed (Images 1 - 2).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the ultrasound findings?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Gallstones obstructing the neck of the gallbladder","Multiple gallbladder polyps","Numerous gallstones and no evidence of acute inflammation","Multiple gallstones with gallbladder wall thickening","Stones in both the gallbladder and common bile duct"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EUltrasonography is the most common and useful imaging modality for gallbladder pathology. The gallbladder should be imaged in two planes, longitudinal and transverse, as shown in the images. There are multiple gallstones lying in the dependent portion of the organ, appearing as hyperechoic foci with posterior acoustic shadowing. The presence of acoustic shadowing is a key feature that helps differentiate stones from \u003Cstrong\u003Egallbladder polyps\u003C/strong\u003E, which do not cast shadows.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile the longitudinal image shows stones in the body and neck of the gallbladder, there is no evidence of \u003Cstrong\u003Egallstones obstructing the neck\u003C/strong\u003E. Ultrasound is a dynamic study, and patients are typically imaged in different positions (supine, lateral decubitus, and erect) to determine if stones are mobile or impacted.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe gallbladder wall measures 1.5mm, which is within normal limits (\u003C3mm). Therefore, there is no \u003Cstrong\u003Egallbladder wall thickening\u003C/strong\u003E, which would suggest acute inflammation. This correlates with the clinical presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile the common bile duct should always be evaluated for size and stones, these images do not demonstrate the bile ducts. Therefore, we cannot confirm or exclude \u003Cstrong\u003Estones in the common bile duct\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe images show \u003Cstrong\u003Enumerous gallstones without evidence of acute inflammation\u003C/strong\u003E, as there is no pericholecystic fluid, gallbladder wall thickening, or oedema. This is the most accurate description of the findings.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Ultrasound is the first line imaging modality for assessing gallstones and gallbladder pathology.","Normal gallbladder wall thickness is less than 3mm; thickening suggests inflammation."],"references":["Gallstones. In: Critical Care Sonography [online]. 2021. Available at: https://www.criticalcare-sonography.com/2016/09/15/large-stone-in-neck-of-gb/","Murphy MC, Gibney B, Gillespie C, Hynes J, Bolster F. Gallstones top to toe: what the radiologist needs to know. Insights Imaging. 2020;11(1):13. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7002643/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63850"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1840"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15298"},{"type":"media","id":"15299"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15298","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15298"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e9855acf-3e8a-46c6-b1e6-bc27e71028df.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e9855acf-3e8a-46c6-b1e6-bc27e71028df.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1282}},{"type":"media","id":"15299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15299"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cc25bc03-5d42-499b-8da8-bf11a481aafc.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/st